canonical:
  title: 美人圖
  author: 李承召
  language: lzh
  text: 閑來相與闘圍碁却被春嬌下子遲手托香腮無限意桃花枝上囀鶯兒
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 美人圖
  author: 李承召
  language: lzh
  text: 閑來相與闘圍碁。却被春嬌下子遲。手托香腮無限意。桃花枝上囀鶯兒。
korean:
  title: 미인도
  author: 이승소
  language: kor
  text: |-
    틈이 나면 서로 더불어 바둑과 싸우다가
    문득 춘교로 바둑돌을 더디 놓네
    손으로 향기로운 뺨을 문지르는 무한한 뜻은
    복숭아꽃 가지 위에는 꾀꼬리가 지저귄다
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1450_020_0210&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Portrait of a Beauty
  author: Lee Seung-so
  language: eng
  text: |-
    When leisure comes, we sit together playing go,
    But spring's enchantress moves her stones so slow.
    Her hand caresses her fragrant cheek with endless grace—
    While orioles sing their songs through peach blossoms' face.
  footnotes:
    - '春嬌 (spring''s enchantress): A poetic reference to a beautiful woman, literally ''spring beauty.'' The term evokes the gentle allure of springtime personified as feminine charm.'
    - '圍碁 (go): The ancient board game of strategy, serving here as a device to capture an intimate moment of distraction and beauty interrupting concentration.'
